{
  "texts": [
    "Anscombe's answer is that it is the idea of a process extended across time and structured towards a goal.",
    "This idea can be illustrated with what is maybe her most famous example: the man pumping poisoned water into a building and thereby poisoning a group of politicians inside it, with the goal in so doing to bring about a change in regime and a good government.",
    "In her discussion of this example, Anscombe (pp.",
    "37-49) points out two things: a) that of the many ways of describing what is happening, there are plenty that could equally well be used to pick out the action the man is engaged in doing, and b) these descriptions fall into an order structured by the question 'Why?'",
    "such that one description can be used to answer the question asked of another (e.g., Q: 'why are you pumping the water?'"
  ]
}